reviews.text:
A quaint diner located in the heart of downtown.  The menu and ambiance bring a flood of memories back as there are featured historical photos everywhere.
The service was excellent and the food was fresh and very tasty.
This is a hidden gem among all of the restaurants along the street...I highly recommend making a stop. 
My BLT sandwich was loaded with crisp bacon and fresh veggies...So good...
I will definitely dine here again.

We had a quick lunch prior to participating in an afternoon concert.  The open face roast beef sandwich has real mashed potatoes!  And the BBQ meatloaf sandwich was tasty. This is a nice diner, with a bar as an unusual complement to the food.  You can get breakfast any time, and have a Mimosa to go with it! Prices are reasonable, too. Busy place but you're attended to by several waitstaff, including  (I think) the owner.
Great dinner experience and breakfast all day. You will need to add your own salt/pepper to the food. Indoor and outdoor seating!

Classic 1951 diner with a mix of traditional and updated Southern fare. We had "four egg" omelets; I'd have to guess small eggs. Nicely prepared. Not much cheese, but the vegetables were plentiful and lightly cooked. Good coffee that keeps on coming.

Really quaint old-school diner. Two of my kids got afternoon breakfast (the pancake order is enormous) and the rest of us got sandwiches. Everything tasted good and we had leftover pancakes in the morning.

So I had my order delivered to West Duluth. My delivery driver was very prompt, even though he forgot my soda at the store, he went and grabbed some at the nearest convenient store. Now that is service! I have never had a bad experience with Pizza Luce, but this last experience will definitely make me order more often from them! Kudos to their delivery drivers.

We ordered in, it got to us in the time they said it would , but our pizza seemed old , half cold and taste wasn't even close to amazing. same with our cheesy bread, not impressed.. the only thing we ate the most of was the wings. For how expensive it was I thought it was going to be amazing, it was not. I definitely will not eat here again. Again, I am not impressed with the experience 🤦

I was in town for a work meeting and the whole team went here for lunch. For a large group and a busy lunch schedule they still got our food to us quickly. The food was worth the visit and the ambiance was awesome.

One of my favorite restaurants in Duluth. We could not decide on which pizza to order so the server suggested that we get 2 different kinds on 1 pizza. It was perfect for us and the food was delicious as usual.
So many great vegetarian, vegan, dairy and gluten free options! Gluten free stuffed shells were amazing. Molly bar was very good. Great and quick service and very reasonable prices.

安くて美味しい！
飲み放題付き3,000円のコースは、お料理もいっぱい出てきて、ボリューム満点！
とむや
飲み放題メニューも種類が豊富で、色々なお酒を試せたり、ノンアルメニューも多かったです
辛さも控えめで食べやすいし、テーブルにタバスコのようなソースもあったので、調整もできます
店員さんも感じ良かったです
居酒屋わやわやの姉妹店。熟成白神生ハムを売りにしている。単品699円テーブルサーブだと1000円。国産三元豚使用‼️添加物一切不使用‼️
3,500円のコースでお腹いっぱい食べられます。ただしハイボールは炭酸が抜けた感じでイマイチ

手軽にアジアン料理を食べられるお店です。
メニューが豊富で、何かしら好きなものにありつけます。
パクチー嫌いな人も楽しめます。
ただ、週末は予約しないと入れなさそうです。
飲み放題メニューも多く、料理のコスパも高い。平日の夜でも混んでいました。

The food here is excellent! A lot of very diverse options with lots of variety for all tastes. The prices are great! I had three custom tacos that were a decent size and spent less than $10. I'm from Phoenix, AZ and I highly recommend this place!

This is my favorite taco place in the Cleveland area. Love taking people from out of town here. The food is all really good and they always have awesome unique drinks on the menu. The different shells for the tacos really make this place unique. Can't wait to come back.

Amazing service!  We brought six kids and four adults here for lunch and the staff was incredible. We were blown away by the friendliness and attention given to us to make our lunch so awesome. The food was delicious as always and came out very quickly. The chips were constantly refilled which kept the kids very happy. The french toast was delicious!  The only tricky part was parking. We used the valet service from the hotel next door because street parking was restricted. The hefty valet fee was more than worth it though because we had such a great experience. Thank you, Barrio!!

Serve and food was awesome! The Cher concert let out, and the place was instantly flooded. The staff was amazing. Service wasn't interrupted at all. They sailed through the challenge with ease. Food was spot on. I would definitely go back. Loved their flavors. Perfect pricing.

I love the ambience. The way the natural light hits during the day makes it bright. Such a great place to catch up with friends. Everything on the menu is delicious. Worth it all. 5 stars.Worth giving it a try! Definitely coming back!
